d=%E5%87%B6%E7%84%B0\">凶焰</a> [ <a class=\"pinyin tone1 \" href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/mp3/xiong1.mp3\">xiōng</a> <a class=\"pinyin tone4 \" href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/mp3/yan4.mp3\">yàn</a> ]: ferocity; aggressive arrogance","purpleculture_tree":"<div class=\"tree\"><ul><li><span class=\"str_def\">⿰</span> <span class=\"str_desc\">Left to right</span><ul><li><span class=\"str_def\"><a class=\"dictips\">火</a></span> <span class=\"str_py\">[ <a class=\"pinyin tone3 \" href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/mp3/huo3.mp3\">huǒ</a> ]</span> <span class=\"str_desc\">fire, flame; to burn; anger, rage</span></li><li><span class=\"str_def\"><a class=\"dictips\">臽</a></span> <span class=\"str_py\">[ <a class=\"pinyin tone4 \" href=\"https://www.purpleculture.net/mp3/xian4.mp3\">xiàn</a> ]</span> <span class=\"str_desc\">pit, hole</span></li></ul></li></ul></div>","purpleculture_img":"https://www.purpleculture.net/images/stroke/973981036.jpg","heisig_chinese_memo":"If there is a fire brewing under a pothole, a big flame might burst out at some point.","Ru_trainchinese":"<span class=\"trainchinese-pinyin\">yàn</span>: (<span class=\"trainchinese-type\">графема</span>) <span class=\"trainchinese-transl\">пламя</span>","chinese_mnemonics_deck__meaning":"flame","chinese_mnemonics_deck__story":"If there is a fire brewing under a pothole, a big flame might burst out at some point.","chinese_mnemonics_deck__diagram":"<img src='lf_28976.gif'/>","chinese_mnemonics_deck__kind":"both","humanum_full_description_en":"From the sound of &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%81%AB\">fire</a> &quot; and &quot;<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%87%BD\">臽</a>&quot;, the original meaning is flame. Northern Zhou Yuxin&#39;s &quot;Fu Zhu Fu&quot;: &quot;Light and cold enter, flames and dark wind pass.&quot;<br><br> &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%84%B0\">Flame</a> &quot; can mean shining. Bei Zhou Yuxin&#39;s &quot;Lamp Fu&quot;: &quot;The moving scales are on the whale, and the flames are on the crowing crane.&quot;<br><br> &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%84%B0\">Flame</a> &quot; also means burning. Tang Zhang read the sixth volume of &quot;Xuanshizhi&quot;: &quot;So there are many generations, looking for the light at night, and looking down at it. The light comes out of the earth, like a fire.&quot;<br><br> &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%84%B0\">Flame</a> &quot; can also be compared to momentum. Song Liuyuangang&#39;s &quot;《Anthology of Yan Lu Gong&#39;s Works》 After Preface&quot;: &quot;Looking at what is played and discussing things, first of the chief Bai&#39;s scribbles, the infant is against the scales, the tomb is in flames, and the resistance is not taboo.","humanum_short_description_en":"From the sound of &quot; <a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%81%AB\">fire</a> &quot; and &quot;<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%87%BD\">臽</a>&quot;, the original meaning is flame.","humanum_full_description":"從「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%81%AB\">火</a>」，「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E8%87%BD\">臽</a>」聲，本義為火苗。北周庾信〈對燭賦〉：「光清寒入，燄暗風過。」<br> <br> 　　「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%84%B0\">焰</a>」可表示照耀。北周庾信〈燈賦〉：「動鱗甲於鯨魚，燄光芒於鳴鶴。」 <br> <br> 　　「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%84%B0\">焰</a>」還表示燃燒。唐張讀《宣室志》卷六：「於是里人數輩，夜尋其光，俯而觀之，其光自土而出，若焰薪火。」<br> <br> 　　「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word==%E7%84%B0\">焰</a>」還可比喻氣勢。宋留元剛《＜顏魯公文集＞後序》：「觀所奏論事，先白長官之疏，嬰逆鱗，陵焰勢，抗言不忌。」","humanum_short_description":"從「<a href=\"http://humanum.arts.cuhk.